sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>(Jupyter Notebook)
    participant SDK as CodeFlare SDK<br/>(Python Library)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP, 10001/TCP
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pods
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 1: Cluster Creation

    User->>SDK: Cluster(ClusterConfiguration)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: GET kueue.x-k8s.io/v1beta1/localqueues<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: Default LocalQueue name
    SDK->>SDK: Generate RayCluster YAML<br/>from base-template.yaml
    SDK->>SDK: Wrap in AppWrapper<br/>(if appwrapper=True)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: POST workload.codeflare.dev/v1beta2/appwrappers<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: AppWrapper created
    Kueue->>K8sAPI: Admit workload<br/>(queue scheduling)
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Reconcile RayCluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create head pod
    KubeRay->>RayWorker: Create worker pods
    RayHead->>RayWorker: GCS connection<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 2: Job Submission

    User->>SDK: cluster.job_client.submit_job()
    SDK->>K8sAPI: GET route.openshift.io/v1/routes<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: Ray Dashboard Route URL
    SDK->>Router: POST /api/jobs/<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Router->>RayHead: Forward to Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP
    RayHead->>RayWorker: Distribute work<br/>Ray protocol
    RayWorker-->>RayHead: Task results
    RayHead-->>Router: Job status/logs
    Router-->>SDK: JSON response
    SDK-->>User: Job status

    Note over User,RayWorker: Flow 3: TLS Certificate Generation (Optional)

    User->>SDK: generate_cert.generate_tls_cert()
    SDK->>K8sAPI: GET secrets (ca-secret-*)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: CA cert + key
    SDK->>SDK: Generate client cert<br/>RSA-2048, SHA-256<br/>signed by cluster CA
    SDK-->>User: TLS cert files<br/>(tls-{name}-{ns}/)
    User->>RayHead: RAY_USE_TLS=1<br/>10001/TCP mTLS
